        "reasoning_content": "The most likely pan/drag non-proportional feel comes from two concrete issues:I see the core issues you're pointing out: the pan and drag don't feel proportional, and the text input should follow the cursor rather than sit at a fixed offset. Using the Cont payload version and supporting drag-out makes sense too.\n\nTo fix the non-proportional feel, we should use world-space deltas consistently for both pan and drag. For pan, we calculate the world delta from consecutive world_mouse samples and adjust the camera accordingly. For drag, we apply the screen delta divided by zoom to move the object under the cursor.\n\nFor text input, it should indeed follow the mouse position, so we can update the text position based on the current world_mouse or screen position.\n\nRegarding the Cont payload, we'll switch to that and ensure drag-out is supported by checking if the drag exceeds certain bounds or if the object is moved outside the viewport.\n\nLet me outline the changes:\n\n1. **Update mouse tracking**: Ensure last_world_mouse and current_world_mouse are calculated correctly using 世界坐标转换.\n\n2. **Pan logic**: On MMB press, update last_world_mouse to current. On hold, apply pan delta.\n\n3. **Drag logic**: For RMB drag, use world delta to move the object.\n\n4. **Text input**: Attach text to mouse position, updating it every frame based on mouse.\n\n5. **Cont payload**: Switch to Cont payload version for better performance.\n\n6. **Drag-out support**: Add checks to see if drag goes beyond viewport and handle accordingly.\n\nThis should make both pan and drag feel proportional and consistent, with text following the mouse naturally. Let me know if you want me to implement any specific part in more detail! \n\nWhat do you think about these changes? Should we prioritize any particular fix first? Or do you have any other concerns about the current implementation? I'm here to help refine this further.",
