        "role": "assistant",
        "reasoning_content": "The VM loop is `for(;;) imp();` where each native ends by setting `imp` via `cont()` -> `cvm_exec`. If a native returns without calling `cont()` or setting `imp`, the next loop iteration re-runs the s...I see the issue now. The problem is that `cond_payload` is calling `cvm_exec_payload` but then returning immediately without calling `cont()`, so the main loop just keeps re-running the first instruction of the action block forever. That’s why it freezes and eventually exits.\n\nThe fix is simple: after successfully dispatching the action, you need to call `cont()` so the VM can advance past the `cond_payload` instruction and continue with the next program instruction.\n\nIn `cond_payload` when `ok` is true, change it to:\n\n```c\nif (ok) {\n    cvm_exec_payload(h);\n    cont // <-- add this\n} else {\n    cont();\n}\n```\n\nThat should let the VM finish the action block and move on. The frame-saving logic you spotted is probably why it eventually blows up after many iterations — once frames hit 1024, `cvm_ret` stops working and the loop hangs or crashes.\n\n 1. program hits cond_payload.run\n 2. ok=true, cvm_exec_payload(action_key) \n 3. cvm_exec finds block, cvm_set_current(action block), start_fn(first instr of action)\n 4. cvm_exec returns, cvm_exec_payload returns, cond_payload.run returns WITHOUT calling cont()\n 5. main loop: imp() runs first instruction of action - good\n 6. action instructions continue via cont\n 7. action ends with zero token, cont does cvm_ret() which restores ptr to AFTER cond_payload, then cont() continues next program instruction\n\nWait - when action ends cvm_ret restores ptr to cond_payload instruction cont() advances past it. Good! But wait - when action ends, we're in cont() of the last instruction of the action. That last instruction's cont advances to zero terminator of action block, then cvm_ret, then cont() again with ptr = cond_payload. That cont advances past cond_payload. OK.\n\nSo cond_payload path might work for successful exec...\n\nBut compare with old cond:\n```\nif (ok) cvm_exec(h);\nelse cont();\n```\nSame pattern - no cont after success. So same behavior as before.",
