        "content": "根因是 `cond_payload` 走了会就地改写 payload 的 `cvm_exec_payload`，把动作逻辑 key 写成内容 hash，还把正在跑的 program 缓存弄脏，过一会儿就会崩；中键平移也随之失效。正在改成不改写的 `cvm_exec` 路径并重新安装。",
        "reasoning_content": "The critical issue is clear now:\nThe problem is exactly what I suspected — the rewrite is mutating the live program cache in a way that breaks the hash consistency the server relies on.\n\nWhen `cond_payload` succeeds, it does:\n```c\nmemcpy(p, oldh, 32);  // p was the action key, now overwritten with content 32-byte hash\n```\nSo the program memory now contains the content hash instead of the action key. But the server still thinks the block is keyed by the original action key. When `cvm_cache_verify_async` fires (every 30s), it uploads the mutated block back to the server under the original key — 32 bytes of garbage instead of the real action key. That’s why it eventually exits: the server rejects the corrupted block or the client tries to re-download a broken version.\n\nThe second issue (pan/actions after first run) is the same root cause: once the payload becomes a content hash, `cvm_resolve_payload hash` no longer finds the correct block because the key is now wrong.\n\n### Quick fix (works today)\nSwitch back to `const_payload` + `cond` for the action path. That’s what the old design used and it never mutated the program stream. You can keep `cond_payload` for other things, just not for logical action keys.\n\n### Better long-term fix (if you really want `cond_payload`)\nMake `cond_payload` take the **content hash** directly instead of the logical key. That way the rewrite step is a no-op (because the payload is already the hash). You’d just need to change the 3 lines that call `cond_payload` to pass the resolved content hash instead of the action key.\n\nOr the minimal code change:\n```diff\n- cvm_exec_payload(k);\n+ {\n+   uint8_t tmp[32];\n+   memcpy(tmp, k, 32);\n+   cvm_exec(tmp); // use copy so payload is never mutated\n+ }\n```\nThis keeps the payload intact while still using the fast path.\n\nEither way, the program cache will stay consistent and pan/clicks will keep working after the first run. Let me know which direction you want to go and I’ll give you the exact patch.",
