        "reasoning_content": "There's a potential bug: pan uses world_mouse which depends on camera. At pan time, camera was set at frame start. Then we update CAM vars. Then we camera_set again. Then sample world_mouse for last_*...I see the issue now. The pan logic is still using the old world_mouse (which depends on the camera state at the moment of sampling), and the camera update is happening after that sample. So when the mouse is held still, the world_mouse stays the same, but the last_world was sampled with the previous camera — if the camera changed during the frame, the delta isn't zero and you get a small jump.\n\nThe cond_payload drag-out is basically the same math but with an extra layer: it treats the payload as a \"virtual\" last position that follows the mouse until it's dropped, then snaps back to the last known position.",
